        <mxCell id="e13" value="⑫ mailbox signals (event-driven)" style="edgeStyle=orthogonalEdgeStyle;rounded=1;html=1;endArrow=block;fontSize=10;strokeColor=#5B7FBF;fontColor=#31507F;" edge="1" parent="1" source="func" target="corch"><mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry"/></mxCell>
        <mxCell id="legend" value="&lt;b&gt;How it interacts&lt;/b&gt;   ① Teams SSO + @mention   ② web/API over HTTPS   ③ the console proxies every call to the backend, injecting a &lt;b&gt;bot-key-trusted identity&lt;/b&gt; so the orchestrator enforces RBAC &amp; per-deal need-to-know   ④ model inference via managed identity   ⑤ read/write the single deal record (Blob default · Cosmos optional)   ⑥ provision the per-deal Teams channel + SharePoint data room and generate Word/Excel &lt;b&gt;on-behalf-of&lt;/b&gt; the user   ⑦ proactive Adaptive Card alerts   ⑧ M365 Copilot &amp; hosted agents call /mcp (Entra OAuth)   ⑨ keyless market data (SEC · GLEIF · GDELT)   ⑩ Entra validates SSO/OBO   ⑪ managed-identity auth (no secrets)   ⑫ event-driven mailbox signals" style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;whiteSpace=wrap;fontSize=10;fontColor=#31507F;fillColor=#F7FAFF;strokeColor=#B9CDE8;rounded=1;spacing=8;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="40" y="872" width="1400" height="110" as="geometry"/></mxCell>
